race.comment: LAMBAY (7) was quickly back on track when belting the CL3 graders in a strong Showcase at Gundagai. That was expected and the well-bred gelding will be fitter again. Has weight relief, and he's the one to beat. URAFIKI (8) couldn't have been more impressive, winning a Moruya Open 3 first-up and then was outgraded at monster odds at Randwick. That was ambitious, and she's going to be much sharper back home with the tongue tie on for the first time. Needs a good ride but is the likely threat. IMASUPERSTAR (6) resumed improved and is proven second-up. Maps to get every chance and is well in the mix. STARLIGHT GIRL (5) always puts in and just missed at Queanbeyan 7 days ago. Uses the rail and the tongue tie is applied for the first time. She'll get every chance.
